Architecture:
Internet ---> Google Load Balancer ---> Google Managed SSL Certificate ---> GKE Ingress ---> Service ---> Pod

Implementation
###Update ingress.yaml to this:
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: app-ingress
  annotations:
    networking.gke.io/managed-certificates: app-cert
    kubernetes.io/ingress.class: "gce"
spec:
  rules:
    - host: app.deeptechexpertconsulting.com
      http:
        paths:
          - path: /
            pathType: Prefix
            backend:
              service:
                name: app-service
                port:
                  number: 80

#### Creatge Managed Certificate Resource ---> add this below to helm
apiVersion: networking.gke.io/v1
kind: ManagedCertificate
metadata:
  name: app-cert
  namespace: payments
spec:
  domains:
    - app.deeptechexpertconsulting.com

#### Point to DNS
kubectl get ingress -n payments

A record
app.deeptechexpertconsulting.com → 34.171.88.130

#### Wait for certificate provisioning
kubectl describe managedcertificate app-cert -n payments

#### Test
curl https://app.deeptechexpertconsulting.com
